title: Arsenal news: Tottenham still ten years behind Gunners, says Martin Keown | Metro News
text:
Louis Sealey for Metro.co.uk Sunday 26 Feb 2017 12:46 pm Tottenham last finished ahead of Arsenal in 1995 (Picture: Getty) 
Tottenham are still 10 years behind north London rivals Arsenal despite their encouraging progress under Mauricio Pochettino, according to Martin Keown. 
Spurs have failed to finish above Arsene Wenger’s Arsenal since 1995 and blew the chance to get one over the Gunners last season. Jurgen Klopp sends warning to his Liverpool flops after Leicester loss 
Pochettino’s charge looked genuine title contenders last term but a dismal run ensured they eventually finished third behind Arsenal and surprise champions Leicester. 
Tottenham made a strong start to the current campaign and are currently ahead of Arsenal on goal difference, but Keown insists his former club remain the powerhouse in north London. 
‘They’re 10 years behind Arsenal,’ the former England defender told BT Sport. ‘The Wembley effect, we did that, and it was never going to be successful for them. 
‘I don’t think Spurs fans should get too far ahead of themselves. They have a smaller squad, and that’s due to financial constraints. Mauricio Pochettino’s Tottenham are ahead of Arsenal on goal difference (Picture: Getty) 
‘They’re building a brand-new stadium. We’ve already heard about that from Arsenal and how restrictive that was, so they already have that to contend with.’
